On October 31 Barnaul police discovered two gambling halls.
The first one operated in the Industrial district on Vzletnaya street.
A game was underway in the facility during the inspection.
There were 24 machines in the club.
Another gambling club was discovered in the Lenin district on Anton Petrov street.
Here they used 20 gambling machines.
The Barnaul administration of the Russian Ministry of Internal Affairs reports that administrative materials have been compiled based on the article "Unlawfully organizing and conducting gambling".
Equipment was confiscated.
Soon materials on these facts will be sent to the courts of the Industrial and Lenin districts of the city.
